&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Karbon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Karbon is the global leader in AI-powered practice management software for accounting firms. We provide an award-winning cloud platform that helps tens of thousands of accounting professionals work more efficiently and collaboratively every day. With customers in 40 countries, we have grown into a globally distributed team across the US, Australia, New Zealand, Canada, the United Kingdom, and the Philippines. We are well-funded, ranked #1 on G2, growing rapidly, and have a people-first culture that is recognized with Great Place To Work® certification and on Fortune magazine&#39;s Best Small Workplaces™ List.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Karbon is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Mid-Level&lt;/strong&gt;, Fullstack Software Engineer. This is an exciting time to join the team because we are expanding our organization. In this role, you will be working within an agile development team to design and build interactive web applications. They are responsible for technical specifications and developing and deploying software. &lt;strong&gt;This role is focused on our API and Integrations team, with a lean towards Front-end.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build and maintain product features - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Develop new functionality and iteratively improve existing systems, with a focus on reliability, performance, and user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Balance speed and quality - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Know when to move fast and when to slow down, making thoughtful trade-offs to deliver high-quality outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use data to inform decisions - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Learn from user behaviour, experiment thoughtfully including A/B testing where relevant, and help improve acquisition and conversion over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work effectively as part of a team - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Collaborate closely with engineers and QA throughout the development cycle to build, test, and improve features together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use AI tools thoughtfully - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Leverage AI to move faster for example drafting code, exploring solutions, or writing tests, while applying good judgement and always reviewing what ships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work with autonomy - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Take ownership of problems, explore solutions, and ask questions when needed rather than waiting for predefined answers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own your work - &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Take pride in what you build and feel accountable for its impact on customers and the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bring your whole self - &lt;/strong&gt;Contribute your curiosity, creativity, and personality to an open, and collaborative team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We know great engineers come from many backgrounds. You don’t need to tick every box below to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid frontend skills with experience using Javascript/Typescript and frameworks such as React.js, Angular.js, Vue.js, &lt;a href=&quot;http://ember.js&quot;&gt;Ember.js&lt;/a&gt; or equivalent. Comfortable working across the full stack and building rich, interactive user interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong fundamentals and hands-on experience building web applications using C#, .NET (MVC, Web API, .NET Core a plus)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of RESTful APIs and how data flows through distributed systems, including designing and consuming web APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with SQL Server or relational databases, and an understanding of how data flows through an application&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Karbon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Karbon is the global leader in AI-powered practice management software for accounting firms. We provide an award-winning cloud platform that helps tens of thousands of accounting professionals work more efficiently and collaboratively every day. With customers in 40 countries, we have grown into a globally distributed team across the US, Australia, New Zealand, Canada, the United Kingdom, and the Philippines. We are well-funded, ranked #1 on G2, growing rapidly, and have a people-first culture that is recognized with Great Place To Work® certification and on Fortune magazine&#39;s Best Small Workplaces™ List.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People Business Partner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
