&lt;li&gt;Challenge leaders constructively, balancing strong support with the willingness to push back when decisions carry people or business risk, using data and AI-generated insights to back your position when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage people data and analytics to build narratives that drive leadership alignment. You use AI to go deeper and faster, and bring insights to the table, not just reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive specific value-add HR projects as needed to continuously elevate our overall people function and offering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a change champion, guiding and supporting leaders through change when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with People Ops and our Talent Team to deliver a seamless employee experience across the full lifecycle, and contribute to global People initiatives across Karbon&#39;s seven regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years as an HR Advisor/People/HR Business Partner with a strong HR Generalist foundation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior SaaS or high-growth tech experience is essential. You understand how Engineering and Product orgs operate and what drives delivery and team health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Australian employment law, Fair Work, modern award interpretation, and WHS.&lt;/li&gt;
